/*the keyword public is necessary before class because we want to allow
 * other programmers (the public) to use the new class
 * 
 * Syntax: always use a capital letter for the first character of names of new classes
 * 
 * The rest of the class definition, between the two bracks {} is a list of all the components of the class
 * 	+these components are called members of the class (3 types)
 *			-instance variables
 *			-constructors
 *			-methods
 */
public class Throttle {
	/* 
	 * 
	 */
	//the topmost position of the lever
	private int top;
	//the current position of the lever
	private int position;
}
